main event: An unidentified object was observed near Albuquerque, New Mexico on June 11, 1964.
interesting points: The object was observed for 10-15 seconds,It was reported to have appeared solid and metallic,The object's flight was described as straight and level with flashing features,The conclusion of the report states it was not a balloon, aircraft, or satellite,The observation was solely visual with no physical evidence collected.
